# Cursor — Frontend Testing

Authoritative source: [docs/ai/frontend/testing.md](mdc:docs/ai/frontend/testing.md).

## Where tests live

`src/frontend/src/tests/` mirrors `src/frontend/src/`. Never co-locate a
`.spec.ts` next to the source.

```
src/frontend/src/lib/services/exchange.services.ts
                       ↳ src/frontend/src/tests/lib/services/exchange.services.spec.ts
src/frontend/src/btc/services/btc-send.services.ts
                       ↳ src/frontend/src/tests/btc/services/btc-send.services.spec.ts
```

- Reusable mocks → `src/frontend/src/tests/mocks/<thing>.mock.ts`.
- Reusable test utilities → `src/frontend/src/tests/utils/<thing>.test-utils.ts`.
- Reusable fixtures → `src/frontend/src/tests/fixtures/`.

## What to test

- All `*.utils.ts` — they're pure, easy, valuable.
- All `*.services.ts` — happy path + each error branch.
- All `*.derived.ts` — at least the non-trivial ones.
- All shared / reused components (and any component with logic).
- Bug fixes — the PR must contain a regression test that fails on `main`.

Coverage thresholds are enforced by CI (`vitest --coverage`) and
auto-updated upward by `frontend-update-coverage-thresholds.yml`. Don't
lower them.

## Stack

- Vitest 4 + `@testing-library/svelte` + `jsdom`. Configured in
  [`vitest.config.ts`](mdc:vitest.config.ts) and
  [`vitest.setup.ts`](mdc:vitest.setup.ts).
- Mock helpers: `vitest-mock-extended`, `fake-indexeddb`.
- e2e is Playwright (`e2e/`), currently in **maintenance-only** mode
  (see below).

## E2E (Playwright) — temporarily restricted

The suite under [`e2e/`](mdc:e2e/) is unreliable for non-trivial flows
right now. Default for agents:

- **Do not add new Playwright specs** unless the user asks, or unless
  it is a trivially stable spec mirroring an existing one.
- For browser-only bugs / changes, **document manual repro steps in the
  PR body** instead of writing an e2e.
- Existing snapshot regeneration follows
  [HACKING.md "E2E visual comparisons"](mdc:HACKING.md). The full e2e
  job is gated by the `run-e2e-snapshots` label and a nightly cron.

When the suite is restored, this rule flips and
[docs/ai/frontend/testing.md#e2e-status-temporarily-restricted](mdc:docs/ai/frontend/testing.md)
is updated in the same PR (meta-update rule).

## Conventions

- One `describe` per module under test; nested `describe` per public
  function. One `it` per behaviour, named from the caller's perspective.
- Reset mocks in `beforeEach`. Never let test order matter.
- Prefer existing mocks from `$tests/mocks/**.mock.ts` over building your
  own. If you build a new one, put it under `tests/mocks/` so the next test
  reuses it.
- Stub network with `vi.stubGlobal('fetch', mockFetch)` +
  `vi.unstubAllGlobals()` in `afterAll`.

## Forbidden

- `it.skip` / `describe.skip` / `it.todo` left on `main`.
- Real network calls.
- `setTimeout`-based waits — use `vi.useFakeTimers()` / `waitFor` /
  helpers in `$tests/utils/timers.test-utils.ts`.
- Hard-coded English assertions when an i18n key exists. Assert against
  `get(i18n).…` instead.
- `console.log` debug noise in committed tests.

## Run

```bash
npm run test                                                  # all (sharded in CI)
npm run test -- src/frontend/src/tests/path/to/file.spec.ts   # one file
npm run test:debug                                            # logging enabled
npm run test:coverage                                         # with coverage
```

CI shards into 20 parallel jobs and merges coverage. Don't write tests that
depend on shard order or filesystem state across files.
